    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "yes, it's really the client type that is a little more restrictive than needed. Does having a ts-ignore have an impact on any site though?\r\n\r\nThe correct type is ```ReadonlyArray<readonly number[]> | `${number},${number},${number},${number}`;```, and then the ts-ignore could be ignored, when the algoliasearch requirement is set to the version in which that fix is done",
